The capital city is Outapi. The region is home to the Ruacana Falls. Omusati is also home to the Omugulugwombashe Heritage Site. This is where the Namibian struggle for independence started in 1966. The region has twelve constituencies: * Anamulenge * Elim * Etayi * Ogongo * Okahao * Okalongo * Onesi * Oshikuku * Otamanzi * Outapi * Ruacana * Tsandi ==References== Category:Regions of Namibia
